      "content": "It's generally not recommended to take clarithromycin with simvastatin at the same time. Clarithromycin can interact with statins like simvastatin, potentially increasing the risk of muscle damage and other side effects. To minimize these risks, it's best to take the statin in the morning, and the clarithromycin at night, about 12 hours apart. This way, the effects of one medication won't interfere with the other.",
